    <item>
      <title>Cake Debate - Jeff&amp;#039;s ACWW Blog</title>
      <author>Jeff</author>
      <link>https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/07/11/cake-debate/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/07/11/cake-debate/</guid>
      <pubDate>Sat, 12 Jul 2025 03:55:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;article id="post-8243" class="post-8243 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-uncategorized"&gt; 	&lt;header class="entry-header"&gt; 		&lt;h1 class="entry-title"&gt;Cake Debate&lt;/h1&gt;	&lt;/header&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-header --&gt;  	 	 	&lt;div class="entry-content"&gt; 		 &lt;p&gt;On Wednesday, Robin told me that she&amp;#8217;s happiest when she can relax in her own home&amp;#8230;on a pizza.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img fetchpriority="high" width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/07/11/cake-debate/Array" alt="Robin: I'm at my happiest when I can relax in the comfort of my own home...on a pizza." class="wp-image-8244" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;figcaption class="wp-element-caption"&gt;I&amp;#8230;almost&amp;#8230;agree.&lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Filbert asked me to deliver a letter to Truffles, because he doesn&amp;#8217;t trust the post office to get it to the right person.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/07/11/cake-debate/Array" alt="Filbert: I'd be so embarrassed, my head would probably burst into flames, bucko!" class="wp-image-8245" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Even though Filbert didn&amp;#8217;t want anyone other than Truffles to read it, Truffles was eager to read it with me. 😆&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/07/11/cake-debate/Array" alt="Truffles: Hey, bunny, let's read it together, on my Wii!" class="wp-image-8246" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;In the letter, Filbert admitted to eating a 20-pound cherry delight. When I told him the delivery was done, he rewarded me with a stone wall.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Yesterday, I listened in on a conversation: Caroline asked Truffles what kind of cake she would be, if she could be a cake. 😆&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/07/11/cake-debate/Array" alt="Caroline: Hey, Truffles. If you could be any cake in the world, what would you be?" class="wp-image-8247" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Truffles already knew the answer. She&amp;#8217;d be a carrot cake. 🥕&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/07/11/cake-debate/Array" alt="Truffles: Oh, that's easy. Carrot. What, did you think I wasn't going to have an answer?" class="wp-image-8248" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Truffles said she thinks about this all the time, and she said she&amp;#8217;d have a delicious frosting hat.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/07/11/cake-debate/Array" alt="Truffles: Dude, I think about this ALL THE TIME. I'd have a delicious frosting hat." class="wp-image-8249" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Caroline said that she might be a cheesecake because she likes cheese, but she hasn&amp;#8217;t put much thought into it. Truffles scolded her for not planning for situations like this. This game is so crazy sometimes.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/07/11/cake-debate/Array" alt="Truffles: Oh, Caroline, this isn't the sort of thing you can leave to chance..." class="wp-image-8250" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Today, Tank&amp;#8217;s replacement moved in. Say hello to Pippy the rabbit.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/07/11/cake-debate/Array" alt="Pippy: Evening! I'm Pippy. I gotta say, I just love to walk around." class="wp-image-8251" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I kind of like her, but she&amp;#8217;s definitely not one of my favorites. It&amp;#8217;s funny though, how villagers can remind you of people (former friends, for example) that really liked that villager.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Even though I do extended bug-catching sessions in Wild World like I do in &lt;a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=EFnEZqWVqjg" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener"&gt;City Folk&lt;/a&gt;, I did catch a couple of elephant beetles tonight.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/07/11/cake-debate/Array" alt="I caught an elephant beetle! The heavyweight of beetles!" class="wp-image-8252" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Have a good weekend, everyone! And good luck with your summer bug hunting, if you&amp;#8217;re into that. 🪲&lt;/p&gt; 	&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-content --&gt;  	&lt;footer class="entry-footer"&gt; 		&lt;span class="byline"&gt;&lt;img alt='' src='https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/07/11/cake-debate/Array' class='avatar avatar-49 photo' height='49' width='49'/&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Author &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="author vcard"&gt;&lt;a class="url fn n" href="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/author/jvgsjeff/"&gt;Jeff&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="posted-on"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Posted on &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/07/11/cake-debate/" rel="bookmark"&gt;&lt;time class="entry-date published" datetime="2025-07-11T23:55:00-04:00"&gt;July 11, 2025&lt;/time&gt;&lt;time class="updated" datetime="2025-07-12T00:25:07-04:00"&gt;July 12, 2025&lt;/time&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;			&lt;/footer&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-footer --&gt; &lt;/article&gt;</description>
      <media:content url="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/robin-pizza3.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Sustainable Forest Fires - Jeff&amp;#039;s ACCF Blog</title>
      <author>Jeff</author>
      <link>https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/07/05/sustainable-forest-fires/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/07/05/sustainable-forest-fires/</guid>
      <pubDate>Sun, 06 Jul 2025 03:57:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;article id="post-13490" class="post-13490 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-uncategorized"&gt; 	 	&lt;header class="entry-header"&gt; 		&lt;h1 class="entry-title"&gt;Sustainable Forest Fires&lt;/h1&gt;	&lt;/header&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-header --&gt;  	&lt;div class="entry-content"&gt; 		 &lt;p&gt;On Wednesday, I received Robin&amp;#8217;s moving-out letter in the mail. She doesn&amp;#8217;t call it a goodbye, because she&amp;#8217;s sure we&amp;#8217;ll meet again somewhere. And that&amp;#8217;s probably more true than she knows, since she also lives in my Wild World town.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img fetchpriority="high" width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/07/05/sustainable-forest-fires/Array" alt="To: Jeff, I've decided to move away from Forest. It's hard to say bye to good friends like you. So I won't. Because I'm SURE we'll meet again somewhere! -From: Robin" class="wp-image-13492" sizes="(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;While nosing through Antonio&amp;#8217;s things, I got this curious message that said &amp;#8220;Let&amp;#8217;s just pretend we didn&amp;#8217;t see that&amp;#8230;&amp;#8221; Except that I could literally see that nothing was inside. 😛&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/07/05/sustainable-forest-fires/Array" alt="...Let's just pretend we didn't see that, shall we?" class="wp-image-13493" sizes="(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;figcaption class="wp-element-caption"&gt;What&amp;#8217;s in the box?&lt;br&gt;Nothing! Absolutely nothing!&lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Rosie approached me and gave me a free regal wall. She was on her way to throw it out, but she said it&amp;#8217;s better to recycle anyway.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/07/05/sustainable-forest-fires/Array" alt="Rosie: I'm, like, totally concerned about greenhouse flashes and sustainable forest fires or whatever!" class="wp-image-13495" sizes="(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;figcaption class="wp-element-caption"&gt;This sounds like Lindsay Bluth.&lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Later on, I held my first bug-catching session of the summer. I started shortly before 11 p.m., because I know more of the valuable bugs come out at 11:00. However, I was a bit disappointed when it suddenly started to rain right when the clock struck eleven! I wasn&amp;#8217;t sure which of the bugs the rain would prevent from appearing.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;However, I shouldn&amp;#8217;t have worried. I was seeing a lot of scarab beetles, and a good mix of the other regular summer bugs too. But the rain also had a positive side-effect: It allowed me to catch two coelacanths!&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/07/05/sustainable-forest-fires/Array" alt="A coelacanth?" class="wp-image-13494" sizes="auto, (max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;In slightly over an hour of bug-catching (and a little fishing too), I made about 250,000 bells.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Today, Nana sent me a letter telling me that she was over her cold. She sent me an office locker to say thanks for the medicine I&amp;#8217;ve been giving her lately.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;I went over to the Roost to check out K.K. Slider&amp;#8217;s Saturday night show, and he performed &amp;#8220;Comrade K.K.&amp;#8221; for me.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/07/05/sustainable-forest-fires/Array" alt="K.K.: All right, get ready to dig the riffs on this ditty: Comrade K.K.." class="wp-image-13496" sizes="auto, (max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Monty asked me for a new catchphrase, and I wanted him to say &amp;#8220;it&amp;#8217;s poop.&amp;#8221; However, the game wouldn&amp;#8217;t let me say that. So I added an extra &amp;#8220;o&amp;#8221; and then it worked out just fine. 😛&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/07/05/sustainable-forest-fires/Array" alt="Monty: Wander around on a day like this one, and see what you discover, it's pooop." class="wp-image-13497" sizes="auto, (max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;While I haven&amp;#8217;t yet recorded a bug hunting gameplay session video yet for 2025, I will be doing that soon&amp;#8230;perhaps by next week.&lt;/p&gt; 	&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-content --&gt;  	 	&lt;footer class="entry-footer"&gt; 		&lt;span class="posted-on"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Posted on &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/07/05/sustainable-forest-fires/" rel="bookmark"&gt;&lt;time class="entry-date published" datetime="2025-07-05T23:57:00-04:00"&gt;July 5, 2025&lt;/time&gt;&lt;time class="updated" datetime="2025-07-06T02:32:39-04:00"&gt;July 6, 2025&lt;/time&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="byline"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Author &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="author vcard"&gt;&lt;a class="url fn n" href="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/author/jvgsjeff/"&gt;Jeff&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;			&lt;/footer&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-footer --&gt;  &lt;/article&gt;</description>
      <media:content url="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/RUU_8277-sm.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Blue, Cornered, Multifaceted - Jeff&amp;#039;s New Horizons Blog</title>
      <author>Jeff</author>
      <link>https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/07/05/blue-cornered-multifaceted/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/07/05/blue-cornered-multifaceted/</guid>
      <pubDate>Sun, 06 Jul 2025 03:44:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;article id="post-8853" class="post-8853 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-uncategorized"&gt; 	 	&lt;header class="entry-header"&gt; 		&lt;h1 class="entry-title"&gt;Blue, Cornered, Multifaceted&lt;/h1&gt;	&lt;/header&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-header --&gt;  	&lt;div class="entry-content"&gt; 		 &lt;p&gt;On Sunday, Quillson the duck was camping here in Forest for the 2nd time. I ducked out before he could inquire about moving in.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img fetchpriority="high" width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/07/05/blue-cornered-multifaceted/Array" alt="Quillson, at the campsite: Hey, you're a local, right? The name's Quillson. Ha HA! That's how I laugh." class="wp-image-8855" sizes="(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;On Wednesday, Louie sent me a letter with a blue corner attached. Since it was Agent S&amp;#8217;s birthday, I thought that would make a good gift for her. It is blue, after all. So I wrapped it up and headed to the squirrel superhero&amp;#8217;s party. But when I gave her the present, there was a problem: She said she already has a blue corner! Oops!&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/07/05/blue-cornered-multifaceted/Array" alt="Agent S: The thing is...I totes have a blue corner already." class="wp-image-8856" sizes="(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;However, she still accepted it. Another squirrel, Static, was also at the party. And he even called himself &amp;#8220;an old cuss.&amp;#8221; 😆&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/07/05/blue-cornered-multifaceted/Array" alt="Static: Seein' someone have that much fun is enough to make even an old cuss like me smile! C'mon, let's celebrate!" class="wp-image-8857" sizes="(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Yesterday, I listened in on a conversation between Agent S and Bones. Agent S said that her goal was to become a multifaceted pop star, and Bones didn&amp;#8217;t understand. 😛&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/07/05/blue-cornered-multifaceted/Array" alt="Agent S: My goal is to be, you know, a multifaceted pop star." class="wp-image-8858" sizes="auto, (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;  &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/07/05/blue-cornered-multifaceted/Array" alt="Bones: A munchy-fact-ed whatnow?" class="wp-image-8859" sizes="auto, (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Today, I had another camper at the campsite. It was Peggy the pig, but I have no interest in bringing home &lt;em&gt;this &lt;/em&gt;bacon.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/07/05/blue-cornered-multifaceted/Array" alt="Peggy: Hi there! I'm Peggy, and I'm totes camping on your awesome island!" class="wp-image-8860" sizes="auto, (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;K.K. Slider was in town tonight for his Saturday night show, and I asked him for a random song. He performed &amp;#8220;K.K. Rally&amp;#8221; for me, Ankha, Bob, and Bones. Well, and a mosquito.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/07/05/blue-cornered-multifaceted/Array" alt="K.K. Slider performs for Ankha, Bones, Bob, and Jeff." class="wp-image-8854" sizes="auto, (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Here are a few other quick notes about this week:&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;ul class="wp-block-list"&gt; &lt;li&gt;On Sunday, K.K. Slider performed &amp;#8220;K.K. Ballad&amp;#8221; for me.&lt;/li&gt;    &lt;li&gt;On Tuesday, I sold 18 fish to C.J. for a whopping 312,000 bells.&lt;/li&gt;    &lt;li&gt;On Wednesday, Wisp gave me a garden chair when I returned his spirits to him.&lt;/li&gt;    &lt;li&gt;Flick was in town, and I sold him 32 bugs for 159,000 bells.&lt;/li&gt;    &lt;li&gt;Yesterday, I returned a lost item to June. She rewarded me with some cat grass.&lt;/li&gt;    &lt;li&gt;I helped out Gullivarrr, and he sent me another pirate outfit today.&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; 	&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-content --&gt;  	 	&lt;footer class="entry-footer"&gt; 		&lt;span class="posted-on"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Posted on &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/07/05/blue-cornered-multifaceted/" rel="bookmark"&gt;&lt;time class="entry-date published" datetime="2025-07-05T23:44:00-04:00"&gt;July 5, 2025&lt;/time&gt;&lt;time class="updated" datetime="2025-07-06T00:56:40-04:00"&gt;July 6, 2025&lt;/time&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="byline"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Author &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="author vcard"&gt;&lt;a class="url fn n" href="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/author/jvgsjeff/"&gt;Jeff&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;			&lt;/footer&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-footer --&gt;  &lt;/article&gt;</description>
      <media:content url="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/quillson-camper2-sm.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Day of Surprises - Jeff&amp;#039;s ACWW Blog</title>
      <author>Jeff</author>
      <link>https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/07/04/day-of-surprises/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/07/04/day-of-surprises/</guid>
      <pubDate>Fri, 04 Jul 2025 23:09:16 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;article id="post-8228" class="post-8228 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-uncategorized"&gt; 	&lt;header class="entry-header"&gt; 		&lt;h1 class="entry-title"&gt;Day of Surprises&lt;/h1&gt;	&lt;/header&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-header --&gt;  	 	 	&lt;div class="entry-content"&gt; 		 &lt;p&gt;Tuesday was July 1st, and I received my monthly bank statement in the mail. I earned 80,350 bells in interest this month, so I&amp;#8217;m up to 80% of the maximum interest payment now!&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;It was Curt&amp;#8217;s birthday, and I remembered to show up to his birthday party. I gave him some chocolates (from Gulliver) for his gift. Happy birthday, Curt!&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img fetchpriority="high" width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/07/04/day-of-surprises/Array" alt="Curt: Hey! Look at that! Chocolates!" class="wp-image-8229" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;He gave me a wobbelina to thank me. Caroline was also at the party, but she seemed more interested in the cake than anything else.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/07/04/day-of-surprises/Array" alt="Caroline: Nice party, isn't it? I love a good birthday. Well, what I really love is cake." class="wp-image-8230" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;On Wednesday, Truffles told me that Tank and Filbert have the kind of friendship that only guys have: They settle arguments with their fists!&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/07/04/day-of-surprises/Array" alt="Truffles: You know, the kind where you settle arguments with your fists!" class="wp-image-8231" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;If a rhino and a squirrel got into a fist fight, I don&amp;#8217;t think the squirrel has a chance at all. Would a rhino even &lt;em&gt;feel &lt;/em&gt;a punch from a squirrel? I don&amp;#8217;t think so.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Today, I was very surprised to find a goodbye letter from Tank in the mail!&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/07/04/day-of-surprises/Array" alt="Stop cryin', Jeff! I'm hitting the road so I can bulk up my calf muscles. Next time you see me, I'll be RIPPED! Don't cry! -Tank" class="wp-image-8232" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I didn&amp;#8217;t play yesterday, but Tank was walking around outside on Wednesday. So this isn&amp;#8217;t a matter of him being packed up and me just forgetting to go in his house. If he was leaving this soon, shouldn&amp;#8217;t he have been packed up on Wednesday?? I mean, it&amp;#8217;s not like I&amp;#8217;m crushed by Tank&amp;#8217;s departure or anything. But I just don&amp;#8217;t understand how things like this happen without notice when I only skipped one day. 🤷‍♂️&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Caroline asked me to deliver a letter to Drift, and the clock struck 5:00 p.m. as I found him. The letter itself wasn&amp;#8217;t all that interesting (aside from Caroline&amp;#8217;s dream of becoming a badminton referee), but I saw Pete flying overhead in the distance. I was mid-conversation with Drift though, so I had no chance of shooting Pete down. Caroline later rewarded me with a chainlink fence.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Robin asked me for some blue furniture, so I checked out the shop to see what they had. I bought a cooler that was very clearly blue. When I took it over to Robin, she said this:&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/07/04/day-of-surprises/Array" alt="Robin: Hey, about your cooler..." class="wp-image-8233" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I was sure she about to tell me it&amp;#8217;s not blue, and refuse to accept it&amp;#8230;but surprisingly, she didn&amp;#8217;t. (So why did she have to psych me out like that?) She was happy for the cooler, and she rewarded me with a rock guitar (no strings attached).&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;After that, I was about to go into town hall to check the recycle bin and wrap up my game for the day. But Whitney pinged me first, and she surprised me by giving me her photo!&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/07/04/day-of-surprises/Array" alt="Whitney: It's a picture of me! Do I look good or do I look good, all night?" class="wp-image-8234" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;After my quick stop in town hall (the recycle bin was empty today), I went home. I put Tank&amp;#8217;s pic into storage and put Whitney&amp;#8217;s pic on display instead.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/07/04/day-of-surprises/Array" alt="Whitney's pic on display in my house." class="wp-image-8235" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Her favorite quote on the back is &amp;#8220;If you even THINK about crossing me, just think about these pearly whites!&amp;#8221; I never expected Whitney to have one of the most violent quotes in the game. Wow. So much for &amp;#8220;Never Stop Crossing;&amp;#8221; I better stop crossing Whitney right away. 😛&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/07/04/day-of-surprises/Array" alt="Quote on Whitney's pic: If you even THINK about crossing me, just think about these pearly whites!" class="wp-image-8236" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;	&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-content --&gt;  	&lt;footer class="entry-footer"&gt; 		&lt;span class="byline"&gt;&lt;img alt='' src='https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/07/04/day-of-surprises/Array' class='avatar avatar-49 photo' height='49' width='49'/&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Author &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="author vcard"&gt;&lt;a class="url fn n" href="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/author/jvgsjeff/"&gt;Jeff&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="posted-on"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Posted on &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/07/04/day-of-surprises/" rel="bookmark"&gt;&lt;time class="entry-date published" datetime="2025-07-04T19:09:16-04:00"&gt;July 4, 2025&lt;/time&gt;&lt;time class="updated" datetime="2025-07-04T19:14:46-04:00"&gt;July 4, 2025&lt;/time&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;			&lt;/footer&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-footer --&gt; &lt;/article&gt;</description>
      <media:content url="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/curt-bday.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>The Adventure Starts Today - Jeff&amp;#039;s New Leaf Blog</title>
      <author>Jeff</author>
      <link>https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/2025/06/30/adventure-starts-today/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/2025/06/30/adventure-starts-today/</guid>
      <pubDate>Tue, 01 Jul 2025 01:12:11 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;article id="post-18263" class="post-18263 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-uncategorized"&gt; 	 	&lt;header class="entry-header"&gt; 		&lt;h1 class="entry-title"&gt;The Adventure Starts Today&lt;/h1&gt;	&lt;/header&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-header --&gt;  	&lt;div class="entry-content"&gt; 		 &lt;p&gt;The rain recently has put a damper on things, including villagers&amp;#8217; moods. &lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img fetchpriority="high" width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/2025/06/30/adventure-starts-today/Array" alt="Rolf: Whenever the skies aren't clear, my mood gets a little rainy too, at death." class="wp-image-18264" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Lolly even told me that the rain has made her feet soaked and wrinkly&amp;#8230;among other things.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/2025/06/30/adventure-starts-today/Array" alt="Lolly: All the walking I've been doing today has my feet all soaked and wrinkly, if I poop!" class="wp-image-18267" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;figcaption class="wp-element-caption"&gt;This is too much information.&lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Rolf asked me for an orange yesterday, so I found one for him. He loved it, and he rewarded me with a paper wall lamp.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/2025/06/30/adventure-starts-today/Array" alt="Rolf: I am completely satisfied right now! At death!" class="wp-image-18265" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I shot down a balloon present in the rain, and it contained a cupid bench. You gotta &lt;em&gt;love &lt;/em&gt;that. 💘 &lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/2025/06/30/adventure-starts-today/Array" alt="A present falls from the sky after I popped the balloon it was flying on." class="wp-image-18266" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;It&amp;#8217;s as if I was shooting Cupid&amp;#8217;s arrow, and not just a pebble from my slingshot. Regardless, that perfect shot will set a new &lt;em&gt;bench&lt;/em&gt;-mark for slingshot users everywhere. 😛&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;I found a lost item on the ground, and it took me a while to find its owner. But I did eventually return it to Hornsby. He thanked me by giving me a jungle-camo shirt.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/2025/06/30/adventure-starts-today/Array" alt="Hornsby: Here's a thank-you gift for your trouble. I hope you like it. It's a jungle-camo shirt!" class="wp-image-18268" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;With all the rain we&amp;#8217;ve been having in this &lt;em&gt;rainForest, &lt;/em&gt;I&amp;#8217;m sure the jungle-camo will blend right in.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Boots asked me for something to replace his yellow butterfly, but I didn&amp;#8217;t have any small tabletop furniture for him. So I caught a squid for him instead. He was excited about his new pet, and he said the adventure starts today!&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/2025/06/30/adventure-starts-today/Array" alt="Boots: So the adventure starts today!" class="wp-image-18270" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;figcaption class="wp-element-caption"&gt;He rewarded me with a ranch tea table.&lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Today, Boots seemed more interested in eating me! 😲&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/2025/06/30/adventure-starts-today/Array" alt="Boots: I'll eat you!! In a swamp! You've got a rosy glow about you. You must be working out!" class="wp-image-18271" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;He asked me to deliver a gift to Molly, who was close nearby. You can even see her in this screenshot:&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/2025/06/30/adventure-starts-today/Array" alt="Boots: I got this gift for Molly, but I'm too shy to deliver it myself... I'm kind of the strong, silent type." class="wp-image-18272" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;He sent her a round clock, and Molly loved the style. She rewarded me with a sno-cone tank, which I decided to put on for summer.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/2025/06/30/adventure-starts-today/Array" alt="Molly: It's a sno-cone tank!" class="wp-image-18273" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Cube wished me a good evening&amp;#8230;until he realized it was morning, not evening. Maybe he&amp;#8217;s used to seeing me in the evening instead. 😛&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/2025/06/30/adventure-starts-today/Array" alt="Cube: Good evening, cool guy. Wait a sec... It's not evening at all! Let's try that again. Good morning." class="wp-image-18274" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;figcaption class="wp-element-caption"&gt;Maybe he needed the clock more than Molly did.&lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;He asked me to play a game of hide-and-seek, and he gave me 15 minutes to find him, Molly, and Boots. I found Cube within seconds; he was behind a tree right next to the plaza.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/2025/06/30/adventure-starts-today/Array" alt="Cube: Darn. I guess you found me. I never thought you'd look here, on Toy Day." class="wp-image-18275" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;figcaption class="wp-element-caption"&gt;Maybe walk farther than a few feet next time.&lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Less than a minute later, I also found Molly. She was behind the zen bell, and I had found two of the three hiders in one minute.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/2025/06/30/adventure-starts-today/Array" alt="Molly tries to hide behind the zen bell." class="wp-image-18276" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Three minutes after that, I found Boots behind the Sphinx. If he thought that was a good hiding spot, he must be in &lt;em&gt;de-Nile&lt;/em&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/2025/06/30/adventure-starts-today/Array" alt="Boots tried to hide behind the Sphinx." class="wp-image-18277" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Instead of standing up tall like that, he should have tried &lt;em&gt;lion &lt;/em&gt;low.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Cube rewarded me with an exotic table for winning the game. But July is almost here&amp;#8230;is anyone excited about peak summer bug season? I know it&amp;#8217;s not quite the same in New Leaf, since you go to the island and catch summer bugs year-round&amp;#8230; but I think it&amp;#8217;s a fun time of year! I always enjoy catching those big valuable bugs!&lt;/p&gt; 	&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-content --&gt;  	 	&lt;footer class="entry-footer"&gt; 		&lt;span class="posted-on"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Posted on &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/2025/06/30/adventure-starts-today/" rel="bookmark"&gt;&lt;time class="entry-date published" datetime="2025-06-30T21:12:11-04:00"&gt;June 30, 2025&lt;/time&gt;&lt;time class="updated" datetime="2025-06-30T21:31:39-04:00"&gt;June 30, 2025&lt;/time&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="byline"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Author &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="author vcard"&gt;&lt;a class="url fn n" href="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/author/jvgsjeff/"&gt;Jeff&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;			&lt;/footer&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-footer --&gt;  &lt;/article&gt;</description>
      <media:content url="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/20250629_HNI_0001.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Robin Relocates - Jeff&amp;#039;s ACCF Blog</title>
      <author>Jeff</author>
      <link>https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/06/28/robin-relocates/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/06/28/robin-relocates/</guid>
      <pubDate>Sun, 29 Jun 2025 03:58:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;article id="post-13481" class="post-13481 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-uncategorized"&gt; 	 	&lt;header class="entry-header"&gt; 		&lt;h1 class="entry-title"&gt;Robin Relocates&lt;/h1&gt;	&lt;/header&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-header --&gt;  	&lt;div class="entry-content"&gt; 		 &lt;p&gt;Today, I received my bug trophy in the mail, from winning the Bug-Off last weekend. I sold it for 2,450 bells, which is more than I expected it to be worth.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;When I visited Robin, I saw that she is moving out of town&amp;#8230;and spreading her wings. 😆 Maybe she saw the Bat Signal in the sky, and she has to fly.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img fetchpriority="high" width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/06/28/robin-relocates/Array" alt="Robin: I just HAVE to spread my wings, so to speak. But I'm glad I saw you before I left, la-di-da! Take care!" class="wp-image-13482" sizes="(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I&amp;#8217;m okay with her leaving; I do still have her in Wild World, after all.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Back outside, Felicity called me crazy for being up so late&amp;#8230;even though it was only 8 p.m.! But then she realized that she was still up too, so she must be the crazy one. Either that, or everyone else.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/06/28/robin-relocates/Array" alt="Felicity: But I'm up, too... So that means that I'M the crazy one... Or maybe it's just everyone else!" class="wp-image-13483" sizes="(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Biskit was talking about K.K. Slider being at the Roost tonight. But he also was talking about going over there tomorrow to hear a song at lunchtime? K.K. won&amp;#8217;t still be there tomorrow, dawg!&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/06/28/robin-relocates/Array" alt="Biskit: I'm thinking of going over there tomorrow and requesting a good song with my lunch!" class="wp-image-13484" sizes="(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;But speaking of the Roost, I did head over there myself. Monty was in there too, enjoying some coffee.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/06/28/robin-relocates/Array" alt="Monty, at the Roost: The coffee here is rich and mysterious, much like myself." class="wp-image-13485" sizes="auto, (max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I asked K.K. for a random song, and he performed &amp;#8220;K.K. House&amp;#8221; for me and Monty.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/06/28/robin-relocates/Array" alt="K.K.: All right, get ready to dig the riffs on this ditty: K.K. House." class="wp-image-13486" sizes="auto, (max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;It&amp;#8217;s not a bad song; the chorus is the &lt;em&gt;key&lt;/em&gt;, and now it lives &lt;em&gt;rent-free&lt;/em&gt; in my head. 🏠😉&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;It was raining in town tonight, and Rosie was sick of the dampness. She even said if hating rain is bad, she wants to be REALLY bad. 😆&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/06/28/robin-relocates/Array" alt="Rosie: Boooo! If hating the rain is bad, then I wanna be REALLY bad!" class="wp-image-13487" sizes="auto, (max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Nana was sick with a cold today, so I gave her some medicine. Get well soon, monkey brain.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;July starts next week (Tuesday, in fact), and that means prime bug-hunting season is almost here! I&amp;#8217;m wrapping up June with 67,650,000 bells in savings. My summer goal will be to earn 2.35 million more bells, so that I reach 70 million bells by September 1st. That shouldn&amp;#8217;t be a problem with the way I enjoy my summer bug-hunting nights. 🙂 I&amp;#8217;ll also post a video of one of those sessions at some point in July, too.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Good luck with your bug hunting everyone, and I&amp;#8217;ll see you in July! 🦋&lt;/p&gt; 	&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-content --&gt;  	 	&lt;footer class="entry-footer"&gt; 		&lt;span class="posted-on"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Posted on &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/06/28/robin-relocates/" rel="bookmark"&gt;&lt;time class="entry-date published" datetime="2025-06-28T23:58:00-04:00"&gt;June 28, 2025&lt;/time&gt;&lt;time class="updated" datetime="2025-06-29T00:36:11-04:00"&gt;June 29, 2025&lt;/time&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="byline"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Author &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="author vcard"&gt;&lt;a class="url fn n" href="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/author/jvgsjeff/"&gt;Jeff&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;			&lt;/footer&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-footer --&gt;  &lt;/article&gt;</description>
